#This file explain about basic of bash
#bash starts with 'shebang':#!/usr/bin/env bash
# bash file can be executed by "bash filename"
### Some Redirection Operatiors
# | (Pipe output to command)
# > (Redirect output to a file) #example: fine / -name "linux" >out 2>error #>write the message to file #2> write the error message to file name error
# >> (Redirect and append output to a file)
# < (Use a file as input)
# << (Here document:take input until token)
